          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-12 15:05:49" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to cause or instigate divisions between people</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to cause divisions</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>‘To cause divisions’ may be expressed in a number of languages in idiomatic ways, for example, ‘to cause people to turn their backs on one another’ or ‘to cause people to no longer speak to one another’ or ‘to cause people to form parties against one another.’ For another interpretation of ἀποδιορίζω in {S:06500101900008}, see {D:30.116}.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
